<A>__{roderick laughing and paying a bet.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{i lost many a bet to the royal dukes, his majesty's brothers.}
<L>__{exterior field day}
<A>__{reviewing the company of troops. roderick, the earl of crabs, the countess, patrick and brookside, several princes and noblemen and the duke of rutland.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{one of the main causes of expense which this ambition of mine entailed upon me was the fitting out and arming of a company of infantry from the hackton estates, which i offered to my gracious sovereign for the campaign against the american rebels. these troops, superbly equipped and clothed, were embarked at portsmouth in the year 1778.}
